Contractors and masons registered with the National construction authority (NCA) will begin earning continuous professional development (CPD) points in an effort to ensure the multi-billion industry observe quality and integrity. In the initiative that targets local contractors registered under NCA, cement manufacturing companies will be key stakeholders to be used as CPD earning sites with Savanna Cement Company to be used to pilot the project. The capacity building project also aims at imparting skills that enables the contractors understand the key role cement plays in the construction industry. Speaking when contractors and NCA officials toured Savanna cement last Thursday, stakeholders said the initiative will enhance effectiveness and efficiency in construction to avert collapsing of buildings by understanding the cement mixing process.